Talks held between Kim Yong Nam and Li Peng
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Beijing June 3 (KCNA) -- Talks were held in Beijing today between Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, and Li Peng, chairman of the standing committee of the National People's Congress of the People's Republic of China.   At the talks the two sides informed each other of the situation of their countries, exchanged views on further developing the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries and on a series of issues of common concern and reached a consensus of views.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK side referred to the struggle of the Korean people who are triumphantly building a powerful socialist nation despite all difficulties under the Juche-based leadership of the Worker's Party of Korea over the revolution with priority given to the army. The DPRK side also mentioned the principled questions arising in achieving the reunification of the country at an early date, ensuring the peace and stability of the Korean peninsula, settling international problems on a fair basis and adhering to independence.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Saying the DPRK rejoices as over its own over the achievements made by the Chinese people in the building of socialism with Chinese characteristics under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, the DPRK side reclarified the invariable stand of the WPK and the DPRK government to continue to consolidate and develop the Korea-China friendship that struck its roots in the joint struggle and was sealed in blood.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Chinese side stressed the need to develop the Sino-DPRK friendly relations in the 21st century, too, with the joint efforts of the leaders of the two countries and expressed the belief that the Korean people would continue to successfully accelerate the building of a powerful socialist nation in the spirit of self-reliance.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It said China is taking the road of development in conformity with the specific conditions of China, pursuing the foreign policy based on independence and sovereignty, and that it is expressing full support for the Korean people's struggle to achieve peace and stability on the Korean peninsula and its independent and peaceful reunification.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The talks took place in a sincere and amicable atmosphere.
Present at the talks on the DPRK side were Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly= Hong Song Nam, premier of the cabinet= Kim Il Chol, vice-chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and Minister of the People's Armed Forces= Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea and chairman of the SPA= Paek Nam Sun, Minister of Foreign Affairs= Ryu Mi Yong, chairperson of the central committee of the Chondoist Chongu Party= Ju Chang Jun, DPRK Ambassador E.P. To China= Pak Tong Chun, vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs= and suite members.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Present on the Chinese side were chairman  of the standing committee of the National People's Congress of the PRC Li Peng= vice-premier of the State Council Li Lanqing secretary general of the NPC standing committee He Chunlin= Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan= head of the international liaison department of the c.c., the Communist Party of China Dai Bingguo= minister of foreign trade and economic cooperation Shi Guangsheng= Chinese ambassador E.P. To Korea Wan Yongxiang= deputy secretary general of the NPC standing committee Lu Congmin= deputy chief of the general staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army Qian Shugen= and officials concerned.

U.S. "operation plan 5027-98" condemned
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Council for National Reconciliation issued a statement on June 2 denouncing the U.S. imperialists for working out a new plan for a war of aggression called "operation plan 5027-98" and working hard to carry it out.   The statement noted that the "operation plan 5027-98" is a plan for a war of aggression surpassing the former notorious "operation plan 5027" in bellicosity and danger.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The plan  reflects the U.S.'s intention to make a preemptive attack on the north any moment  and sets such an extremely adventurous stage as  "occupation and rule" over someone  after the end  of war, it said, and went on:   What is all the more dangerous is the fact that they  are running amok in the air attack on Yugoslavia which is believed to be a test war, a preliminary war to put the "second Korean war" into practice, while  deploying  large armed forces and war equipment in South Korea under the pretext of  filling up "vacuum" and staging  large-scale war exercises between the U.S., Japan and South Korea almost every day.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As the "operation plan 5027-98" envisages a preemptive attack if there is a "sign"  of movement in the north,  their large-scale war exercises reached such a very dangerous stage that no one can  presuppose when the exercises will turn into a real war.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The "operation plan 5027-98" proves that the U.S.'s outcries for "peace" and "stability" on the Korean peninsula are a hypocrisy and they are the  very ones who bring clouds of war to the Korean nation and the wrecker of peace.     If the U.S.  and the South Korean rulers ignite a war of aggression, they will be burnt to death by fire of justice showered by the Korean people and people's army united in one mind.

Meeting of co-chairmen of Pomchonghakryon held 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- The 9th meeting of co-chairmen of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) was held in Beijing between May 19 and 21.   Present there were chairmen of the north and overseas headquarters of Pomchonghakryon and its secretariat members.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The presidium of the south headquarters of Pomchonghakryon was represented at the meeting through the exchange of documents  owing to the obstruction of the South Korean authorities.   The meeting summed up last year's reunification movement of Pomchonghakryon and discussed this year's working plan and the issue of building the 4th-term co-secretariat.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Adopted there were a resolution on hailing and carrying into  effect the proposal of a joint meeting of the government, political parties and organizations of the north side, a special statement of the co-chairmen of Pomchonghakryon denouncing the U.S. 's war moves and other documents.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The resolution said:   The joint meeting demanded the South Korean authorities put into practice the priorities for dialogue between the north and south -- the abrogation of "cooperation" system with outsiders, discontinuation of joint military exercises, repeal of the "National Security Law" and  ensuring of freedom of the reunification movement and activities of pro-reunification patriotic organizations such as Pomminryon (National Alliance for the Country's Reunification) and Hanchongryon (South Korean Federation of University Student Councils) and public figures.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   If the present "government" truly wants a new phase of dialogue between the north and the south for national concord and reunification, it should immediately put into practice the priorities without any prejudice and political intrigue.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Pomchonghakryon vows to take the lead in carrying into practice the proposal of the joint meeting and struggle to put an end to the tensions on the Korean peninsula and outsiders' domination and intervention and open an epochal phase of national reunification through the great unity of the whole nation this year.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The special statement said the U.S. imperialists should discontinue the anachronistic and adventurous. Korea policy and the war maneuvers against the north at once,  promptly withdraw their aggression forces and military equipment including nuclear weapons from South Korea, make an immediate apology for their responsibility for all misfortunes and sufferings the Korean nation has undergone owing to the division and compensate for them  and no longer interfere in the internal affairs of the Korean nation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It also urged the South Korean authorities not to seek a fratricidal war by clinging to the coattails of outsiders, but confess their wrong flunkeyist and treacherous acts  before the nation and make a policy switchover to national independence.

Reception given on birthday of Raul Castro Ruz
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea gave a reception at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on June 2 on the occasion of the 68th birthday of Raul Castro Ruz, second secretary of the c.c., the Communist Party of Cuba and Minister of the Revolutionary Armed Forces.
   Present on invitation were Cuban ambassador to Korea Jose Manuel Inclan Embade and embassy officials.
Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, and officials concerned were on hand.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Speaking at the reception, Kim Ki Nam said Raul Castro took part in the revolutionary struggle organized and led by Fidel Castro Ruz in his early years, displayed the high organizing ability and fighting spirit in overthrowing the pro-U.S. batiste dictatorial regime and thus made distinguished contributions to the victory of the Cuban revolution.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He continued:   The victorious advance of the Cuban revolution is unthinkable without the revolutionary activities of Raul Castro who has performed great exploits in the work of building the party, the state and the revolutionary armed forces, true to the cause of Fidel Castro.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the leadership of the Communist Party of Cuba led by respected Fidel Castro, the Cuban people are invariably defending the socialist banner in the western  hemisphere of the earth.   The Worker's Party and people of Korea sincerely wish the fraternal Cuban people greater success in the struggle to defend and advance socialism, rallied around the party and the leader.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Jose Manuel Inclan Embade in his speech extended thanks from the bottom of his heart  to the great leader Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Worker's Party of Korea, for arranging a reception on the occasion of the birthday of Raul Castro.   He went on to say:   The Korean people have registered great achievements, overcoming all the difficulties under the leadership of the WPK led by the great Kim Jong Il.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He expressed the belief that the diligent and devoted Korean people would surely build a powerful nation in the future.   Under Kim Jong Il's leadership the Korean people will achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country without fail, true to the behest of the great leader Kim Il Sung, he noted, expressing full support to their struggle.

War exercises of S. Korean rulers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today comes out with a signed commentary denouncing the South Korean warmongers for acting as a shock brigade and vanguard in executing "operation plan 5027-98," a plan of the U.S.  for a second Korean war.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Pointing out that the warmongers have staged one provocative war exercise against the DPRK after another these days, the news analyst of the paper says:   This is an intolerable challenge and provocation against the DPRK which is making every sincere effort for national reconciliation and unity, peace and peaceful reunification.
   They are planned exercises aimed at mastering military conducts for northward invasion under the updated "operation plan 5027-98."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK will never tolerate frantic moves of the South Korean warmongers to militarily stifle the fellow countrymen in the north hand in glove with foreign aggression forces, branding them as "principal enemy."   The South Korean rulers would be well advised to act with discretion, mindful that provocation of war against the DPRK will precipitate their own destruction.

DPRK delegation leaves for China
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea headed by Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, left here today by special plane to pay an official goodwill visit to the People's Republic of China at the invitation of the standing committee of the National People's Congress and the State Council of the PRC.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Among the visiting group were Hong Song Nam, premier of the DPRK cabinet, Kim Il Chol, vice-chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and Minister of the People's Armed Forces= Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea and chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly= Paek Nam Sun, Minister of Foreign Affairs, Ryu Mi Yong, chairperson of the central committee of the Korean Chondoist   Chongu Party= and other officials.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They were seen off at the airport by Pak Song Chol, Honorary vice-President of the presidium of the SPA, Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, Jo Chang Dok, vice-premier of the cabinet, officials concerned, Li Bin, Chinese charge d'affaires ad interim here, and foreign diplomatic envoys.

Minju Joson observes 35th anniversary of June 3 Uprising
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson today carries a signed article marking the 35th anniversary of the June 3 Uprising of the South Korean students and people against the South Korea-Japan "talks" in 1964.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 3 Uprising in which South Korean youth and students took the initiative was a resolute massive protest against the criminal acts of the U.S. and Japanese aggression forces and the South Korean authorities to conclude the aggressive and treacherous  South Korea-Japan "talks" and an eruption of national indignation  against the reinvasion moves of the Japanese militarist forces and the flunkeyist and treacherous acts of traitors, the paper says, and goes on:   The uprising failed, but it frustrated the "talks," dealing  a telling blow to the foreign forces and traitors and demonstrating  the indomitable fighting spirit and heroic stamina of students and people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The "people's government" rulers turned South Korea into a dual colony of the U.S. and Japan by the pro-American  and pro-Japanese flunkeyist and treacherous acts and the policy of dependence on foreign forces unprecedented in history, bound the people to the fetters of colonial slavery and are actively serving as a "shock brigade" of the U.S. 's war provocation moves against the DPRK.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The reality proves that the South Korean people can not extricate themselves from misfortunes and sufferings nor achieve the peace and peaceful reunification of the country without thwarting and frustrating the domination and interference of the foreign forces trampling down the nation's sovereignty and dignity in South Korea and the treacherous acts of the authorities prolonging their remaining days with flunkeyism and dependence on foreign forces.  The desire of the June 3 uprisers, who bravely fought against the aggressors and traitors 35 years ago, should be realised without fail.

U.S. arbitrary act should not be allowed
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today carries a signed article on the arbitrary and despotic practices of the United States for  world domination which are getting more undisguised as regards the Yugoslav crisis.   The article says:   The United States is  using unreasonable pretext to interfere in internal affairs of those countries that go against the grain with it and those regions and countries that are situated in military strategic vantage-points.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is openly resorting to military threat, pressure and aggression, considering strength an almighty means of establishing a U.S.-led unipolar world.   Its arbitrariness is  manifested in acting as it pleases, ignoring the United Nations and other international organizations.   The targets of its arbitrary practices  are small and big countries, international organizations, even "allied nations", and countries in Asia, Europe, Africa and Latin America.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is seeking a way of establishing the sphere of their  domination over the Asia-pacific region in unleashing a war of aggression on the Korean peninsula.   The U.S. war hawks have worked out a new "operation plan 5027-98" and are fully prepared for a preemptive attack on the DPRK.   The U.S. considers its military actions in Yugoslavia as a good opportunity to test up-to-date weapons for the second Korean war and round off its military operation command system.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Unless its arbitrary practices are shattered, neither peace and security of the world can be defended nor can international justice and impartiality can ensured.   The reckless moves of the U.S. to dominate the world should be checked and frustrated.
   The unshakable anti-imperialist independent stand should be maintained and  even the slightest concession and compromise should not be  tolerated.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   One should not harbor the slightest illusion about the U.S. and yield to economic blockade and military pressure.   In order to shatter their arbitrary practices it is necessary to increase self-reliant national defence capabilities.      One should cultivate one's strength and decisively counter any pressure and challenge of the enemies, convinced of the validity of one's cause.
